vi [filename]
press i to insert at the position of the cursor
press :w to write the file
press :w [new filename]  to save as a new file name
press :q to quit
press esc to exit --insert-- mode
search www.safaribooksonline.com/library/view/fedora-linux/0596526822/ch04s04.html


# indent multiple lines 

Select a row with 'V'
move down with 'j'
to indent press '>'


# indent curly-braces

move to cursor to one of the curly braces
press '>' '%'

# paste copy into an indented section 
instead of using 'p', use ']'

# comment out a section of code 

ctrl + v (visual block mode)
select the virtical line of comments you want
Shift + i (captial I)
insert the text you want, i.e #
press Esc (wait for it to update), presss Esc again
